detail.title: Increase Minimum Deposit for Governance Proposals
detail.description: ### Summary We propose to increase minimum deposit for proposals to 20000 QCK. ### Description The current deposit for the offer is 500 QCK, which is very low compared to other Cosmos chains. For this reason, spam proposals are sent. To prevent this, we recommend increasing the deposit amount to 20000 QCK. ### Voting By voting 'Yes' you agree to raise the minimum deposit for governance proposals to 20000 QCK. By voting 'No' you do not agree to raise the minimum deposit for governance proposals to 20000 QCK.

detail.title: Onboard Akash onto Quicksilver
detail.description:
Summary

Akash is open-source Supercloud that lets users buy and sell computing resources securely and efficiently. With Akash, You can deploy your own cloud infrastructure, and you can sell your unused cloud resources to others. You can also buy cloud resources from others, and you can use them to run your applications. This proposal aims to onboard Akash on to the Quicksilver protocol. This will enable users to stake their AKT (Akash's Staking Token) and mint qAKT (uqakt).

Timing

The onboarding of Akash will be effective when the proposal passes at the end of the voting period. It will be added to the Quicksilver front-end shortly after completion.

Voting Outcomes

- If you vote YES on this proposal, you approve onboarding Akash
- If you vote NO on this proposal, you do not approve onboarding Akash

detail.title: Register Sommelier-3 on Quicksilver
detail.description:
Sommelier Finance is a Cosmos SDK-based blockchain that provides risk-managed multichain DeFi strategies. Sommelier is one of the few Cosmos chains with real yield paying for staking rewards, which makes liquid staking particularly important as it allows for a high staked supply by letting staked SOMM be used in DeFi.

The Quicksilver development team proposes onboarding the Sommelier Network onto Quicksilver to allow SOMM holders to liquid stake SOMM and receive qSOMM.

Timing:
The onboarding of Sommelier will be effective when the proposal passes at the end of the voting period. Sommelier will be added to the Quicksilver front-end soon after.

Voting Outcomes:
- If you vote YES on this proposal, you approve onboarding the Sommelier Network.
- If you vote NO on this proposal, you do not approve onboarding the Sommelier Network.

- Bump cosmos-sdk to v0.46.11
- Bump tendermint to cometbft v0.34.27

detail.title: Change mint epoch-identifier param to emit inflation daily
detail.description:
This proposal will affect the inflationary emissions of the Quicksilver chain, by updating the mint/epoch_identifier parameter from 'epoch' to 'day'.

This will have the effect of causing inflation to be emitted daily, instead of the current epochly (three days) schedule.

The emissions calculation of 40m QCK tokens for y1 was calculated based upon the daily schedule, so this change will ensure that inflation is emitted as intended.

 - Voting 'YES' for this proposal, will enable daily inflation minting in line with the predetermined schedule of 40m QCK tokens in Y1
 - Voting 'NO' for this proposal will leave inflation emissions at the schedule of three-daily, resulting in emissions of 16.66m QCK tokens in Y1

detail.description:
Summary

The Regen Network is a community of actors engaging with ecological regeneration, ecological monitoring, verification, distributed computing and technology development, centered around Regen Ledger.

The Regen Community recently passed governance proposal #26 to enable Interchain Accounts, in preparation for onboarding onto Quicksilver.

The Quicksilver development team proposes onboarding the Regen Ledger (regen-1) onto Quicksilver allow Regen stakers to deposit of REGEN (uregen) and receive qREGEN (uqregen).

Timing

The onboarding of the Regen Ledger will be effective when the proposal passes at the end of the voting period. It will be added to the Quicksilver front-end shortly after completion.

Voting Outcomes

- If you vote YES on this proposal, you approve onboarding Regen
- If you vote NO on this proposal, you do not approve onboarding Regen

Timing

The onboarding of the Cosmos Hub will be effective when the proposal passes at the end of the voting period. It will be added to the Quicksilver front-end shortly after completion.

Voting Outcomesn

* If you vote YES on this proposal, you approve onboarding the Cosmos Hub
* If you vote NO on this proposal, you do not approve onboarding the Cosmos Hub
